{"title_page": "2020 Formula Regional Americas Championship", "text_new": "{{Motorsport season|series=Formula Regional Americas Championship|year=2020|previouslink=2019 F3 Americas Championship | footer=<small>Feeder series:<br>[[2020 Formula 4 United States Championship|Formula 4 United States Championship]]}}\n\nThe '''2020 [[Formula Regional Americas Championship]] powered by Honda''' will be the third season for the [[F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale de l'Automobile|FIA]] [[Formula Three|Formula 3]] regional series across North America. The series is sanctioned by [[SCCA Pro Racing]], the professional racing division of the [[Sports Car Club of America]]. The 2020 season will be the first season under the moniker of Formula Regional Americas, after a rebranding to align with the [[F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale de l'Automobile|FIA]] single-seater development pathway.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.f3americas.com/articles/2013524-fr-americas-championship-gets-rebranded-ahead-of-2020-season|title=FR Americas Championship Gets Rebranded Ahead of 2020 Season|website=FR Americas Championship|language=en|access-date=2020-03-10}}</ref>\n\n== Teams and drivers ==\nRelentless Motorsports will be the first Canadian-based team to compete in the series.<ref name=\"Relentless\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.f3americas.com/articles/2013294-first-canadian-based-team-enters-f3-americas-for-2020|title=First Canadian-Based Team Enters F3 Americas for 2020|website=F3 Americas Championship|date=20 December 2019}}</ref>  All drivers compete with [[Honda in motorsport|Honda]]-powered [[Ligier]] JS F3 cars on [[Hankook Tire|Hankook]] tires.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 87%;\"\n!Team\n!{{Tooltip|No.|Car number}}\n!Driver\n|-\n| {{flagicon|USA}} Crosslink/Kiwi Motorsport\n| 9\n| {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Joshua Car]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.f3americas.com/articles/2013068-f4-u-s-champion-joshua-car-confirms-2020-f3-americas-campaign|title=F4 U.S. Champion Joshua Car Confirms 2020 F3 Americas Campaign|website=F3 Americas Championship|language=en|access-date=2019-12-10}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Flagicon|USA}} Momentum Motorsports\n| 16\n|{{Flagicon|USA}} Kent Vaccaro<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.framericas.com/articles/2013559-momentum-motorsports-inks-kent-vaccaro-to-fr-americas-championship-program-for-2020|title=Momentum Motorsports Inks Kent Vaccaro to FR Americas Championship Program for 2020|website=FR Americas Championship|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flagicon|USA}} Wulff Motorsports<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.f3americas.com/articles/2013435-wulff-motorsports-launches-f3-americas-program|title=Wulff Motorsports Launches F3 Americas Program|website=F3 Americas Championship|date=7 February 2020}}</ref>\n| 61\n| {{flagicon|}} TBA\n|-\n| {{flagicon|USA}} Jensen Global Advisors\n| 99\n| {{flagicon|CAN}} Logan Cusson<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.framericas.com/articles/2013542-cusson-returns-to-fr-americas-with-jensen-for-sophomore-season|title=Cusson Returns to FR Americas With Jensen Global Advisors for Sophomore Season |date=18 March 2020|accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flagicon|USA}} Alliance Racing Sponsored by<br>[[Richard Rawlings|Gas Monkey Energy Drink]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.f3americas.com/articles/2013426-alliance-racing-and-gas-monkey-energy-level-up-to-f3-in-2020|title=Alliance Racing and Gas Monkey Energy Level Up to F3 in 2020|website=F3 Americas Championship|date=4 February 2020}}</ref>\n| TBA\n| {{flagicon|}} TBA\n|-\n| {{flagicon|USA}} Global Racing Group\n| TBA\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Linus Lundqvist]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.framericas.com/articles/2013579-linus-lundqvist-targets-formula-regional-americas-championship-title-run|title=Linus Lundqvist Targets Formula Regional Americas Championship Title Run|date=April 1, 2020|accessdate=April 1, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=2| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Newman Wachs Racing]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.f3americas.com/artic