020 Schedule|work=F3 Americas Championship|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 March 2020, the season opening round in Atlanta was postponed due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.framericas.com/articles/2013530-scca-pro-racing-postpones-the-start-of-the-season|title=SCCA Pro Racing Postpones the Start of the Season|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:85%;\"\n! colspan=2| Round\n! Circuit\n! Date\n<!--! Pole Position\n! Fastest Lap\n! Winning Driver\n! Winning Team-->\n! Supporting\n|-\n|rowspan=3| 1\n! R1\n|rowspan=3| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Circuit of the Americas]], [[Austin, Texas|Austin]]\n|rowspan=3| 5\u20137 June\n|rowspan=3| ''[[2020 Formula 4 United States Championship|Formula 4 United States Championship]]''\n|-\n! R2\n|-\n! R3\n|-\n|rowspan=3| 2\n! R1\n|rowspan=3| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Virginia International Raceway]], [[Alton, Virginia|Alton]]\n|rowspan=3| 17\u201319 July\n|rowspan=3| ''[[2020 Formula 4 United States Championship|Formula 4 United States Championship]]''<br>''Formula Race Promotions''\n|-\n! R2\n|-\n! R3\n|-\n|rowspan=3| 3\n! R1\n|rowspan=3| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Barber Motorsports Park]], [[Birmingham, Alabama|Birmingham]]\n|rowspan=3| 31 July\u20132 August\n|rowspan=3| ''[[2020 Formula 4 United States Championship|Formula 4 United States Championship]]''<br>''Radical Cup''\n|-\n! R2\n|-\n! R3\n|-\n|rowspan=3| 4\n! R1\n|rowspan=3| {{flagicon|CAN}} [[Circuit Trois-Rivi\u00e8res]], [[Quebec]], [[Canada]]\n|rowspan=3| 7\u20139 August\n|rowspan=3| [[2020 NASCAR Pinty's Series|NASCAR Pinty's Series]]\n|-\n! R2\n|-\n! R3\n|-\n|rowspan=3| 5\n! R1\n|rowspan=3| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Sebring International Raceway]], [[Sebring, Florida|Sebring]]\n|rowspan=3| 25\u201327 September\n|rowspan=3| ''[[2020 Formula 4 United States Championship|Formula 4 United States Championship]]''\n|-\n! R2\n|-\n! R3\n|-\n|rowspan=2| 6\n! R1\n|rowspan=2| {{flagicon|