 the first time the series will venture outside the United States, with a round set in [[Quebec]], [[Canada]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.f3americas.com/articles/2012868-f3-americas-championship-makes-international-debut-on-the-streets-of-quebec-in-2020|title=F3 AMERICAS CHAMPIONSHIP MAKES INTERNATIONAL DEBUT ON THE STREETS OF QUEBEC IN 2020|website=F3 Americas Championship|language=en|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref>  The final round is set to be held in support of the [[2020 United States Grand Prix]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.f3americas.com/articles/2013289-2020-f3-americas-schedule-revealed|title=2020 F3 Americas Schedule Revealed|work=F3 Americas Championship|date=19 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.framericas.com/events|title=Formula Regional Americas Championship 2020 Schedule|work=F3 Americas Championship|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 March 2020, the season opening round in Atlanta was postponed due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.framericas.com/articles/2013530-scca-pro-racing-postpones-the-start-of-the-season|title=SCCA Pro Racing Postpones the Start of the Season|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:85%;\"\n! colspan=2| Round\n! Circuit\n! Date\n<!--! Pole Position\n! Fastest Lap\n! Winning Driver\n! Winning Team-->\n! Supporting\n|-\n|rowspan=3| 1\n! R1\n|rowspan=3| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Circuit of the Americas]], [[Austin, Texas|Austin]]\n|rowspan=3| 5\u20137 June\n|rowspan=3| ''[[2020 Formula 4 United States Championship|Formula 4 United States Championship]]''\n|-\n! R2\n|-\n! R3\n|-\n|rowspan=3| 2\n! R1\n|rowspan=3| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Virginia International Raceway]], [[Alton, Virginia|Alton]]\n|rowspan=3| 17\u201319 July\n|rowspan=3| ''[[2020 Formula 4 United States Championship|Formula 4 United States Championship]]''<br>''Formula Race Promotions''\n|-\n! R2\n|-\n! R3\n|-\n|rowspan=3| 3\n! R1\n|ro